The paper proposes a novel transfer learning approach for cross-domain recommendation using neural networks as the base model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with recommendation systems, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the transfer of knowledge across domains, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, which could fall under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL).
